The paper deals with mathematical theory of domains for denotational semantics, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The paper addresses questions related to domains and Scott continuous functions, which are concepts in mathematical logic and topology. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with information systems and generalizations of non-reflexive logics, which are topics in artificial intelligence and information theory, respectively. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses Scott topologies and distance functions, which are topics in topology and analysis, respectively. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are also possible sub-categories.
